<br>
nowhere in this Hatch/Kohl S.724 does it say that APCP motors &lt; 62.5g are exempted from consideration for the purpose of total weight calculation, it refers only to APCP 'propellant' weight.  <br>
<br>
all APCP regardless of weight contributes to the 25 lb limit before the LEUP requirement kicks in.  This is further supported by the references to &quot;propellant for purposes of powering recreational model rockets&quot; and &quot;model rocket motors&quot;, without weight distinction<br>
