<br>
so as 0.9 lbs and under do not contribute to 25 lbs, an unlimited number of 0.9 lb motors may be possessed exempt from permitting and regulated storage<br>
<br>
you really have to see a marked-up 18USC40 to get that<br>
<br>
this being the case, a non-permittee never reaches a 25 lb threshold, as it is unlawful for him to acquire motors &gt; 0.9 lbs.   <br>
<br>
ergo the 25 lb limit applies to only permitees' motors &gt; 0.9 lbs <br>
<br>
now MPR and &quot;low end&quot; HPR and their dealers are in from the cold<br>
the balance of HPR, and all AM/EX (where APCP is used) and their dealers are still in in the frigid waters of the north atlantic with no lights in sight<br>
